Definition 2.10:   Let $Y = T \times_H \fh^{\circ} \times \C^{h+1}$ be a local model. By a slight abuse of notation, we call a $T$-invariant function
  $g \colon Y \to \R$ a {\bf $\boldsymbol{T}$-invariant (homogeneous) polynomial} if its restriction to $\fh^\circ \times \C^{h+1}$ is a (homogeneous) polynomial.
