Let \(I\subset\{1,\ldots,r\}\) be the indices corresponding to the components \(X_i\) that dominate \(Y_\kappa\). For \(i\in I\), let $\Gamma_i$ be the generic fiber of $X_i\ra Y_\kappa$, and let \(\Gamma_i^\nu\to\Gamma_i\) be the normalization.

Then the following hold:
